{{Quote|Jaina Solo is on a mission to stop a scientist from offering villains that most terrible weapon: eternal life.|''Star Wars Insider'' 75's synopsis of "'''Or Die Trying'''"|<ref name="Insider75">[[Star Wars Insider 75|''Star Wars Insider'' 75]]</ref>}}
"'''Or Die Trying'''" is a short story by [[Sean Williams]] and [[Shane Dix]] that features the [[Jedi Knight/Legends|Jedi Knight]] [[Jaina Solo Fel|Jaina Solo]] [[Mission to Onadax|infiltrating]] the [[Onadax Droid Technologies headquarters|headquarters]] of [[Onadax Droid Technologies]] on the [[Planet/Legends|planet]] [[Onadax]]. The company has manufactured a [[Human replica droid]] (HRD) that [[Battle of Bakura (28 ABY)|betrayed]] the citizens of [[Bakura/Legends|Bakura]], and Solo hopes to bring them to justice for the crimes committed by their clients. She confronts an [[Stanton Rendar (droid)|HRD]] named [[Stanton Rendar]] and engages him in a discussion regarding the moral implications of [[Immortality/Legends|immortality]] and near-invincibility, but ultimately remains firm in her convictions and prepares to apprehend him. Rendar looses a group of [[Battle droid/Legends|battle droids]] on Solo and sets the compound to [[Self-destruct mechanism/Legends|self-destruct]], but she defeats the [[Droid/Legends|droids]] and escapes while Rendar flees the planet.

"Or Die Trying" included a full-page illustration by [[Leanne Buckley]] in its publication in the [[Star Wars Insider 75|seventy-fifth issue]] of ''[[Star Wars Insider]]''. The issue was made available to subscribers on [[March 19]], [[2004]], followed by a release to newsstands on [[April 6]]. In [[2003]], Williams and Dix had written the [[Force Heretic trilogy|''Force Heretic'' trilogy]], three volumes of [[Star Wars: The New Jedi Order|''The New Jedi Order'']] book series; "Or Die Trying" is set between the trilogy's [[The New Jedi Order: Force Heretic II: Refugee|second]] and [[The New Jedi Order: Force Heretic III: Reunion|third]] installments. The six-page story builds on the [[Canon|continuity]] of ''Force Heretic'' and additionally ties up several loose ends of the ''[[Star Wars]]'' [[Star Wars Legends|Expanded Universe]], such as the fates of [[Dash Rendar/Legends|Dash Rendar]] and [[Guri]] from [[1996]]'s [[Star Wars: Shadows of the Empire|''Shadows of the Empire'' multimedia project]]. "Or Die Trying" was also published in the [[Star Wars: The Official Magazine 59|fifty-ninth issue]] of ''[[Star Wars: The Official Magazine]]'', and later went on to be archived online as part of [[StarWars.com]]'s [[Hyperspace: The Official Star Wars Fan Club|Hyperspace]] fan club. Its characters and events have since been mentioned in several reference guides.

==Plot summary==
{{Quote|Life is all we have, girl. Do you think I'm about to let you take it away from me? I plan to live forever or&mdash;''"<br />"''Or die trying. Yes, very droll.|Stanton Rendar and Jaina Solo|<ref name="Or Die Trying" />}}
[[File:Ordietrying.jpg|thumb|left|225px|Jaina Solo destroys Stanton Rendar's battle droids.]]
In the [[Standard year/Legends|year]] [[28 ABY/Legends|28 ABY]],<ref name="Date" /> [[Jaina Solo Fel|Jaina Solo]]&mdash;a [[Jedi Knight/Legends|Jedi Knight]] of the [[New Jedi Order]]&mdash;is on the [[Planet/Legends|planet]] [[Onadax]] on a [[Mission to Onadax|mission]] to infiltrate the [[Onadax Droid Technologies headquarters|headquarters]] of a company called [[Onadax Droid Technologies|ODT]]. She is part of a group of representatives from the [[Galactic Federation of Free Alliances]] that has come to Onadax from [[Bakura/Legends|Bakura]] after helping [[Battle of Bakura (28 ABY)|foil]] an [[Ssi-ruuvi invasions|invasion]] of that world by the [[Ssi-ruuvi Imperium]]&mdash;the invasion was made possible by a [[Human replica droid]] (HRD) that was in league with the [[Ssi-ruu]]k, and Solo hopes to confront the creators of the [[Droid/Legends|droid]]. After [[Mind trick/Legends|using]] [[The Force/Legends|the Force]] to alter the compound's security guards' perception of her, she enters the main building with a stolen security pass and follows the Force presence of an HRD to a room. The HRD calmly greets her, and Solo asserts that he is responsible for endangering the people of Bakura. The HRD counters that his company cannot be held accountable for what its clients do after receiving HRD bodies and deflects Solo's claims that the HRD procedure allows criminals to indefinitely put [[The galaxy/Legends|the galaxy]] at risk.<ref name="Or Die Trying" />

The HRD introduces himself as [[Stanton Rendar (droid)|Stanton Rendar]], a [[Stanton Rendar|formerly dead Human]] who was resurrected into an HRD body, and tells Solo the history and mission objectives of ODT, also known as Onadax Droid Technologies. Believing that every [[Sentience/Legends|sapient]] being has the right to life, they create HRDs for wealthy clients with wishes of [[Immortality/Legends|immortality]] and use the Ssi-ruuk's [[entechment]] process to transfer their [[Soul/Legends|souls]] into the droid bodies. Nonetheless, they operate in secrecy, believing that the [[Galaxy/Legends|galaxy]] would not understand. Rendar offers Solo an HRD of her own, but she envisions an [[Army/Legends|army]] of invincible [[Dark side of the Force/Legends|dark side]]&ndash;using HRDs and steadfastly refuses. She prepares to apprehend him, but Rendar has anticipated her refusal and sends a group of [[Battle droid/Legends|battle droids]] after her as he flees the planet in a prepared [[Shuttle/Legends|shuttle]]. Solo swiftly destroys them with [[Jaina Solo's lightsaber|her lightsaber]] and is forced to also flee from the exploding building that Rendar has programmed to [[Self-destruct mechanism/Legends|self-destruct]].<ref name="Or Die Trying" />

==Development==
{{Dialogue|Potts|Will there be any E-Book tie-ins to the Force Heretic trilogy? A prologue? Short story between books? Epilogue?|Williams|At this point, none that I'm aware of.|Dix|Interestingly, there was one small section taken from book 3 that we thought would make a nice little e-story, but nothing has been talked about it.|attr=Michael Potts of TheForce.Net interviewing Sean Williams and Shane Dix in 2003|src=<ref name="interview">{{WebCite|url=http://www.theforce.net/jedicouncil/interview/williamsdix.asp|text=Interview with Sean Williams & Shane Dix - Co-Authors of ''REMNANT''|work=[[TheForce.net|TheForce.Net]]|archivedate=20041212054954}}</ref>}}
[[File:Nestledinthemiddle.jpg|thumb|left|300px|"Or Die Trying" takes place between the events of ''Force Heretic II: Refugee'' and ''Force Heretic III: Reunion''.]]
In [[2003]], authors [[Sean Williams]] and [[Shane Dix]] wrote the [[Force Heretic trilogy|''Force Heretic'' trilogy]], three novels that respectively served as the fifteenth, sixteenth, and seventeenth volumes in [[Star Wars: The New Jedi Order|''The New Jedi Order'']] book series.<ref name="Remnant">''[[The New Jedi Order: Force Heretic I: Remnant]]''</ref><ref name="Refugee">''[[The New Jedi Order: Force Heretic II: Refugee]]''</ref><ref name="Reunion">''[[The New Jedi Order: Force Heretic III: Reunion]]''</ref> [[The New Jedi Order: Force Heretic II: Refugee|''Refugee'']], the trilogy's middle installment, features a plot that takes place on Bakura, in which Galactic Alliance representatives [[Han Solo/Legends|Han Solo]], [[Leia Organa Solo/Legends|Leia Organa Solo]], Jaina Solo, and several others discover that the planet's Prime Minister, Molierre Cundertol, has been promised immortality and undergone the Ssi-Ruuvi entechment process in order to have his soul transferred into a Human replica droid. After helping foil his plans, the [[Solo family/Legends|Solo family]] are told by an ally, the [[Ryn/Legends|Ryn]] [[Goure Conor]], to proceed to Onadax and meet with [[Droma|another member]] of the information-gathering [[Ryn Network]].<ref name="Refugee" /> The ''Force Heretic'' Trilogy's concluding novel, [[The New Jedi Order: Force Heretic III: Reunion|''Reunion'']], opens with the Solos already on Onadax.<ref name="Reunion" /> In a 2003 interview with [[TheForce.net|TheForce.Net]], Williams and Dix indicated that they were interested in writing a short story based on a small section of ''Reunion'', but that there had been no official discussion on the subject.<ref name="interview" />

''The New Jedi Order'' wrapped up in [[November]] of 2003 with [[James Luceno]]'s novel ''[[The New Jedi Order: The Unifying Force]]''.<ref name="tuf">''[[The New Jedi Order: The Unifying Force]]''</ref> Nevertheless, Williams and Dix wrote "Or Die Trying," a short story that took place in the [[New Jedi Order era]] between ''Refugee'' and ''Reunion'' but was not officially part of ''The New Jedi Order'' series.<ref name="Reader's Companion ODT">''[[The Essential Reader's Companion]]'' {{C|"Or Die Trying"}}</ref> The story was published in the [[Star Wars Insider 75|seventy-fifth issue]] of the [[Lucasfilm]] magazine ''[[Star Wars Insider]]'', which was released for subscribers on [[March 19]], [[2004]] and to newsstands on [[April 6]].<ref name="SW.com" /> Including a full-page illustration by [[Leanne Buckley]], "Or Die Trying" is a six-page tale that introduces an additional reason for the Solos to have traveled to Onadax: they are following a trail of [[Galactic Credit Standard/Legends|credits]] that Cundertol laundered off of Bakura in order to have his Human replica droid built. Onadax Droid Technologies, the company that built the droid, is known only as "ODT" during the opening pages of the story, an acronym that also applies to "Or Die Trying"'s title.<ref name="Or Die Trying" /> The story was also included in ''[[Star Wars: The Official Magazine 59]]'',<ref name="UK 59" /> and it was later published online for members of [[StarWars.com]]'s [[Hyperspace: The Official Star Wars Fan Club|Hyperspace]] fan club.<ref name="Hyperspace" />

==Continuity==
{{Quote|I'm very interested in tying up loose ends, both because we're coming in toward the climax of the NJO series, and because there are so many places in the Expanded Universe that have been visited once or alluded to but never seen again. Those places fascinate me.|Sean Williams, on writing within the ''Star Wars'' Universe|<ref name="interview" />}}
While they were writing the ''Force Heretic'' Trilogy, Sean Williams and Shane Dix were eager to reintroduce characters and elements from past stories of the ''[[Star Wars]]'' [[Star Wars Legends|Expanded Universe]] that had not appeared in some time and whose fates were unresolved. Williams thus spent time researching dangling story arcs that he felt were ripe for being further explored.<ref name="interview" /><ref name="interview2">{{WebCite|url=http://www.theforce.net/jedicouncil/interview/williamsdix2.asp|text=Star Wars Q&A with Sean Williams & Shane Dix - Co-Authors of NJO Force Heretic Trilogy|work=[[TheForce.net|TheForce.Net]]|archivedate=20041212055730}}</ref> "Or Die Trying" addresses the fates of [[Guri]] and [[Dash Rendar/Legends|Dash Rendar]],<ref name="Or Die Trying" /> major characters from the [[1996]] [[Star Wars: Shadows of the Empire|''Shadows of the Empire'' multimedia project]].<ref name="Shadows novel">[[Star Wars: Shadows of the Empire (novel)|''Shadows of the Empire'' novelization]]</ref><ref name="Shadows game">[[Star Wars: Shadows of the Empire (video game)|''Shadows of the Empire'' video game]]</ref> The [[1998]] [[Star Wars comic books|comic]] series [[Star Wars: Shadows of the Empire: Evolution|''Shadows of the Empire: Evolution'']] had previously established a partnership between Dash and Guri,<ref name="Evolution 5">[[Shadows of the Empire: Evolution 5|''Shadows of the Empire: Evolution'' 5]]</ref> and "Or Die Trying" reveals the fruits of their labors by resurrecting Stanton Rendar in the form of an HRD.<ref name="Or Die Trying" /> Dash had been believed dead by Jaina Solo's [[Parent/Legends|parents]] and [[Luke Skywalker/Legends|uncle]] after the events of ''Shadows of the Empire'',<ref name="Shadows novel" /> and "Or Die Trying" marks the first time that a member of their family learns of his survival and subsequent work done in HRD development.<ref name="Or Die Trying" />

Stanton Rendar had himself been mentioned in several previous ''Star Wars'' works, such as the [[Star Wars: Shadows of the Empire (novel)|''Shadows of the Empire'' novelization]] and the ''[[Shadows of the Empire Sourcebook]]''.<ref name="Shadows novel" /><ref name="Shadows sourcebook">''[[Shadows of the Empire Sourcebook]]''</ref> "Or Die Trying" was the first appearance of his Human replica droid,<ref name="Or Die Trying" /> who went on to be mentioned in such works as [[2006]]'s ''[[The New Essential Guide to Droids]]'',<ref name="NEGTD">''[[The New Essential Guide to Droids]]''</ref> [[2008]]'s ''[[The Complete Star Wars Encyclopedia]]'',<ref name="CSWE">{{CSWECite|III|92|Rendar, Stanton}}</ref> and [[2012]]'s ''[[The Essential Reader's Companion]]'', the latter of which briefly summarizes all of "Or Die Trying".<ref name="Reader's Companion ODT" /> The story also references [[Project Decoy]],<ref name="Or Die Trying" /> an HRD-related project undertaken by the [[New Republic/Legends|New Republic]] in the [[1993]] young reader novels ''[[Mission from Mount Yoda]]'' and ''[[Queen of the Empire]]''.<ref name="Mission from Mount Yoda">''[[Mission from Mount Yoda]]''</ref><ref name="Queen of the Empire">''[[Queen of the Empire]]''</ref>

In ''Force Heretic II: Refugee'', the Solos are told to go to Onadax by Goure Conor in order to meet another member of the Ryn Network.<ref name="Refugee" /> However, "Or Die Trying" states that Jaina Solo has picked Onadax as her target by [[Telepathy/Legends|telepathically]] learning of the world from an associate of [[Rufarr]], Molierre Cundertol's former [[Pilot/Legends|pilot]].<ref name="Or Die Trying" />

